caption: Great food
Had a good experience in here with my daughter. The food arrives quickly and the customer service is just great. Prices are reasonable.
Very quiet place for weekday buffet lunches. Great food with vegetarian options.
I love this place! Our family has enjoyed their creations dozens of times and they are always awesome!

The mint chutney here is amazing and the sole reason I will continue ordering food from this establishment.  The naan is honest and the saag with chicken is ALWAYS on point.  Please help me keep this business alive.
Best Curry I have had in awhile

The paneer makhani was awful.  It looked and tasted as if they spiced up a can of campbells tomato soup.  I threw it away.  The naan wasn’t too bad, even if it was burned a little.  I would not recommend, nor try again.
First-rate environment and super attentive service. The menu was fresh and yummy. Will clearly recommend this place to anyone. Convenient rates and large meals. Keep up the great work.
Not worth it. We had buffet there. No verity, far from taste, nothing was fresh and when we complained about the quality, they had nothing to say

Delicious Indian restaurant on Cordell.  At lunch, both buffet and a la carte available.  Food was tasty and beautifully plated.  Service was friendly and unobtrusive.  Spinach pakoras were a standout, very light on the batter and the fresh spinach coming through wonderfully.  The menu says that they use all halal meat, and the menu also notes which of the many vegetarian options are vegan (a surprisingly large number).
Excellent dosas. Kind staff.
I ate their lunch buffet, and they had a good selection of Indian curry foods and rice.
We ordered Idly and medu vada with chutney sambar today. We could instantly figure out that it wasn't freshly prepared and stored for really long. We would never recommend this place to anyone.
Nice local spot!
Good service, Good environment.
Love this place!!
Very well kept and welcoming restaurant. They serve big portions and for affordable prices. We enjoyed the menu a lot and the staff members were very welcoming and chatty. Recommended.

Ordered from here the other night with high hopes based on previous reviews. However, given the price and the poor quality, we will not be returning. We ordered three different curries (paneer, croquette, and goat), none of which quite hit the spot. The portions were quite small, so we were glad that we ordered 3 dishes instead of one per person. The goat curry was the worst goat curry I've ever had. It was mostly bone and fat, and the little bit of meat that was there was tough and chewy. It was so bad that we couldn't even finish it. If you're going to go here, go with the buffet so that you can possibly find something appetizing.
Very good food and extremely good service
Delicious and very authentic. I want to try everything. Make sure to ask about a the dish you're interested in if you have spice tolerance issues.
I ordered a Lentil crepe with veggies inside it was so delicious! The menu is great for those with dietary restrictions (gluten free, vegan/vegetarian). Highly recommend!!
The food is constantly well prepared and delightful, staff members gives awesome customer service. I loved how neat it is and vibes. I highly recommend this place.
Great place! went there around 630pm on Friday and place was empty, was a little concerned how fresh the food was going to be but ended up being very fresh and tasteful
The food was AMAZING and the fresh baked naan was perfect. It looks fancy inside at first but quickly feels kinda homey after sitting with your food. Their Saturday buffet is definitely a much have.

Seriously delicious food!! Hidden Gem in Bethesda! we order for delivery from here a lot and decided to sit down and eat this afternoon and were not disappointed! If you’re looking for authentic Indian cuisine, this is your place.
Worst biryani
Very very very nice spot a hidden gem. This is my go to Valentine's day spot. The lentil soup is amazing and the buffet has vast assortment of goodness.

Great food but a 1oz shot of Jim beam shouldn't cost $12, that's kind of messed up if you ask me. I mean the 1/5 cost like $10 at the store. I'd expect prices like that at a strip club or on any airplane but to pay that much there is outrageous, it's no wonder their restaurant was completely empty, except for the kids they had run around. Won't be coming back
Amazing flavors!

Bland!! What Indian cuisine taste like they poured everything out of a can? It was my first and last visit. Don’t eat there if u like Indian foods. This place for those tastebuds that don’t know better.
To pricey. Food was good, but when I'm paying $15-$19 per kabob, I'm expecting more than 5 pieces of meat.
It was ok.
Worst food and worst service
Online orders are never acknowledged, very poor service on that front.  They "realize" an online order came in when you enter to pick up.

The food is DELICIOUS! I’ve tried their amazing Thukpa soup, their version of Korma, and an amazing DomKa (hope I’m saying that right). Everything was made to order (not mass precooked) and made me wonder why I haven’t previously made this my go-to Indian restaurant in Bethesda.
Food is ok and main problem is no parking
Terrible.  Missing things in my order.  Called and said they were too busy and would refund me later.
Had expected a much better draft selection. No salads on food menu whatsoever.

So the food is authentic and amazing. I brought my mom and dad here and they agreed that the food was solid and tasted great. the spinach pakora, bhel Puri and papri chat we are all a great way to start the meal. the coffee and tea were authentic. the rasa Malai and gulab jamun are great. the one problem... service is slow and the sweet proprietors need a little help on how to mak sure everyone's drinks and food comes out at the same time. if you are not in a hurry and want great Indian food.. definitely come here!
Decent food.. prices a bit higher end for that type of food quality
Excellent food!  We had the butter chicken and the vegetable korma, both were fabulous.  The mint chutney was unlike any other I had.  It was more creamy and very spicy, it was excellent!

Went down to woodmont triangle to go to Kadhai but it was so busy we left. Went over to curry kitchen for the buffet and it was fantastic! Delicious tender lamb dish, great butter chicken - more complex flavor than elsewhere. Great rice, samosas, and paneer dish. Would definitely go back.
Mediocre. Found metal pieces baked into our naan. Fortunately noticed something shiny before taking a bite and pulled it out. Won't be going back.
Great food but restaurant doesnt have a liquor license.

Absolutely terrible! I went there for some good Indian food & I got 1 scoop of rice with 4 pieces of chicken cubes they call it "tandoori chicken". What a mess?!?! I will never step here again. I told the lady that served us she didn't even try to make it right she went to say some just give you the rice only. Are you kidding me who wants to pay $17 for a scoop of rice with 4 cubes of chicken. No kidding that's all I had.

Not impressed! Now I'm not saying I won't go back,  but I know there are better Indian restaurants out there.  Some of the food was lacking a little in flavor, and not a single thing was spicy enough, nor did they have any authentic spicy sauce of some sort, to the point of where they made some spicy curry paste to mix in with all the dishes.  If you order a bottle of wine, don't expect to see the bottle first or taste it,  they open it and start pouring the glass as they are walking to your table.  They are a little overpriced for an Indian restaurant of their stature, but they are in Bethesda!

First experience with Indian food, and it was great!! I loved the buffet style setup! It gave us a chance to try everything without having to take multiple trips to the restaurant. It also wasn't super expensive, which my husband enjoyed lol

Worst indian buffet ever! The food is not good but the thing that made it worst is the the waiter working there! He stared at me like crazy! He was following every single step of me to everywhere and he seemed very unhappy of me going to the buffet for the third time! I told him what is wrong why you keep looking at me like a creepy stalker and he couldn’t understand what I am saying!  And the food has really bad taste and they used very low quality meats. Never ever will go there again
Went for lunch buffet - nicely decorated, relaxed atmosphere, great food! We did not feel rushed at all. Service was excellent!

I have no complaints about the food. The food was very tasty. However I am unhappy about their service. I had gone there with a 2 month old & requested for a bigger table so that I could use some extra space for the car seat. They refused even though they just had one guest in the whole restaurant and in an hour they were closing. The place is a little clumsy
Worst ever had
(Translated by Google) I love your meals good attention  (Original) Me encanta sus comidas buena atención
Delicious food
Tasty food with vegan options
Tasty Food , can try
Great food! Not the best place for dine in.
Good food and service.  The restaurant seems to be family owned and the attention and service is great.
Taste of Pani Puri and Paneer Makhni was bad
Probably the best Indian food ever. Very quiet and calming. The staff is very friendly, professional and helpful. My fav is the chicken and coconut the spicier the better
Good food. Nice atmosphere. Love it.
Perfect
Run by an adorable family. Sambar is so good!
Wide variety of excellent food and friendly service in a comfortable environment
Amazing rasmalai and lunch buffet for a great price!
Never again here
Good food.

Maybe the most bland rice I've ever had at an Indian restaurant.  The curry dishes were also lacking in flavor.  I asked for some heat and didn't get it.  Perhaps the south Indian food they serve is ok, but the curry and rice was very dissapointing.
Worst food. Don't try
Good food - had the tandoori salmon. Service was a little slow, but not bad. Good selection of meals, good portion sizes.
Very good food
Good authentic eats.. good amount of food. Great location. Not sure why this location was not filed up on Saturday night !!!!

Tasty food, friendly service. This is simultaneously a good restaurant for a family meal or a date night. Dinner for two was complete with an samosas, naan, a sampler platter, and finished off with chai.
Excellent food, though the service was spotty.  Comfortable ambience.
The food at this place is incredible. The service is very good and the prices affordable. Definitely a staple for our family.
The food was delicious and I was full but didn't feel overly stuffed. Was definitely satisfied. Our server was pretty attentive as well.
Tasty Indian food at a reasonable price. The chai was just ok, but the food was flavorful and well presented.
The food is delicious! Can't wait to be back!

This is the closest to homemade Indian cooking I've found in the metropolitan area. Every sauce tastes different and the quality is consistent. I keep coming back for tasty, non-greasy and satisfying fare.
Favorite Indian place in Bethesda for their lunch buffet. They always have wonderful Naan bread and Butter Chicken along with great service!
Excellent service and delicious food, very satisfied with their lamb
Always friendly, always fast, always very tasty!  They are happy to modify anything.  They are knowledgeable about their menu items.  We love it!

I went here only based on high reviews. Initially, finding parking was a pain and took 20 minutes after which parked in a public garage 4 blocks away. Then started ordering. The staff was good but food was no more than just ok. Serving portions was much smaller than other places and the quality was not good enough.  Naan was burned and dry (i can vouch that Haldiram's frozen garlic naans are significantly better). Given this, the prices were at par with other awesome places. Overall it was a disappointment and wont go there again. I noticed most other reviews as well as the presence were not from people from indian origin who may be less aware of the authentic indian food.

Fantastic experience here.  My brother and I had a few specific requests (and also got great input from them on choices).  They made great recommendations and the food was fantastic.  We will definitely be back.  Strongly recommend a visit.

Excellence in everything they do. We came just as they opened in Saturday afternoon, but I feel we would have gotten a great service even at a busier time. Even though it's not on the menu, we asked for Puri bread and they made it just right. The main course of Chicken Tikka Masala and Coorgi Chicken and the deserts - Kulfi and apricots with cream were also delicious.
Family-owned and operated, we love coming for the lunch buffet!

Loved it. Came for dinner and had a masala dosa and delicious Kofta curry. They were both excellent and extremely well spiced. The prices were cheaper than lots of other Indian restaurants in bethesda. Also very kid friendly. Will def come back.
Thoroughly enjoyed Bethesda Curry Kitchen-wonderful dosas, and the lunch buffet is delicious! The space is clean, light-filled and pleasant. I will be going back often.

Excellent choice for people eating gluten free.  The South Indian cuisine includes dumplings and breads which are rice or lentil.  I had the buffet and the food was fresh and delicious with many great options.

I decided to try the lunch buffet and was glad I did. The selection of items was a bit different from the other Indian restaurants in town and I liked that they had dosa on the menu though I haven't tried them yet. My lunch was delicious and everything was well prepared. The dining area is basic but serviceable. I've come back for lunch a couple of times now.

I have eaten at every highly rated Indian restaurant in D.C. and the Maryland suburbs. The Bethesda Curry Kitchen rates with the best. The crepes were astoundingly delicious, the crepe itself light and the fresh vegetables in the filling were perfectly cooked and seasoned. The sauce in our chicken dish was rich and complex, the chicken succulent.The restaurant looks fairly modest from the outside, but the cooking is fabulous.

Nice Indian Restaurant. Serving up pretty tasty Southern India cuisine. I liked that they asked me how spicy I liked my chicken curry entree. I noted how about London spicy (Indian in London is fantastic, better than anything in the States)? She smiled and I heard her tell the kitchen regular (authentic?) heat lol. Curry dish was tasty with a nice amount of heat than most places. Enjoyed the garlic naan as well (extra item). Mango Lassi was fine but nothing out of the ordinary. Good presentation and nice service. Space is fine, perhaps could use some more color (but they've only just opened). I'll be back to try their lunch buffet specials.
Great new restaurant. Loved the food. If you like coconut/curry/spicy you have to have the Coorgi Chicken. It was amazing.
